1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,640
Our appointment to FEMA should be
finalized within the week.

2
00:00:02,760 --> 00:00:05,060
I've already discussed the matter with the
Senate.

3
00:00:05,560 --> 00:00:07,100
I take it he was agreeable?

4
00:00:07,520 --> 00:00:09,280
He didn't really have a choice.

5
00:00:09,920 --> 00:00:10,920
Has he been infected?

6
00:00:11,540 --> 00:00:12,540
Oh, yes.

7
00:00:12,760 --> 00:00:13,520
Most certainly.

8
00:00:13,740 --> 00:00:17,100
When I mentioned that we could put him on
the priority list for the Ambrosia

9
00:00:17,101 --> 00:00:20,220
vaccine, he was so willing it was almost
pathetic.

10
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:22,972
This play, the rioting,
is intensifying to the

11
00:00:22,973 --> 00:00:24,960
point where we may
not be able to contain it.

12
00:00:25,694 --> 00:00:26,593
Why contain it?

13
00:00:26,700 --> 00:00:29,200
Let it spill over to the schools and
churches.

14
00:00:29,201 --> 00:00:31,300
Let the bodies pile up in the streets.

15
00:00:31,580 --> 00:00:33,980
In the end, they'll beg us to save them.

16
00:00:34,480 --> 00:00:36,800
I've received reports of armed attacks on
shipments.

17
00:00:36,980 --> 00:00:38,576
There's not enough vaccine to go around.

18
00:00:38,600 --> 00:00:40,600
And the underclasses are starting to get
desperate.

19
00:00:41,080 --> 00:00:42,600
Of course they're desperate.

20
00:00:42,601 --> 00:00:44,060
They can smell their death.

21
00:00:44,061 --> 00:00:48,000
And the sound they'll make rattling their
cage will serve as a warning to the rest.

